Comfortable, spacious design hotel 5-minutes walk to the Malacca Museum Complex.
You come here for the panoramic views of Helsinki.
An institution in Helsinki, one must come here to enjoy the beautiful ambiance indoors or outdoors. They have a separate asparagus menu card during spring.
Not only a place to shop for produce and gourmet stuff but a great place to have brunch or lunch!
Love this art nouveau chateau hotel. The bed is like home, the rain shower is to look forward to. Those 'Glo Art Bites' at the lobby lounge bar are yummy!
A beautiful open secret of Helsinki =)
Cool period style interior of the restaurant, nice outdoor terrace. Had Vana Tallinn Coffee, must try when in Tallinn.
Great place if you are a cafe and history enthusiast. The oldest cafe in   the country with the interior left unchanged since a century ago. Check out as well its Marzipan Museum Room.
Reasonably priced very good food in nice ambiance setting.
Comfortable chalet apartment with pool, hammam and sauna located across the Moulin Bejamin lift.
Definitely a place to stop by. A very elegant cafe along the river Salzach with views to the old city and the fortress. The outdoor terrace is lovely during warmer days.
Went to the Mozart Dinner Concert. You really come here for the Mozart classical concert and the Baroque Hall than for the food. Still worth it.

location.neighborhood: Neben Dom, direkt neben Kirche zu St.Peter

tip.text: The live entertainment brought the dinner to a different level. Loved the opera songs! The fregola was my favourite and the antipasti buffet was lovely (anchovies and salami, ummm)
The stunning vaulted interior and the golden ambiance are enough reason to have a drink, snack or lunch at this restaurant.
Best place to have a drink and do some people watching at Odeonsplatz but don't forget to check out the old world charm interior of the cafe.
I had paella which was quite okay and their pita breads were very good. Because of its location, this restaurant is best for drinks during the day and for people watching.
Best cafe terrace with an amazing view in the French Alps at Col de la Madeleine.
One of the best alfresco dining in the city, if not for the views (marina bay and singapore skyline) and ambiance.
Nice place, free sunbeds, good music, cool people, lovely setting (garden on the beach).
Amazing architecture inside the hotel, lines were smooth and mesmerising, although I find the interior design - colours too loud, patterns too busy to the eye and too much bling. Totally blinged out.

tip.text: Very cool. Take your time and enjoy the beautiful beasts because the tunnel is not that long.
The plate of mezze for our starter was also lovely!
Loved the saganaki prawns in ouzo and cream sauce.
Great lounge bar, cool music and lovely atmosphere.
Food was quite good (had the snails and grilled vegies) and the terrace on the water is just lovely. Definitely a place to drop by, either to eat or drink.
The mussels saganaki was lovely. This restaurant on the beach is always busy every night and there is a reason why =)
The lounge bar is great for afternoon coffee/tea or pre-dinner cocktails. The garden terrace would be lovely for the summer.
affordable, very tasty and quality food in an industrial design space setting on the water. the lamb was gorgeous.
Lovely place to stop for a cup of coffee after some shopping at Solaris.  Cosy main cafe area and beautiful views from the rooftop terrace.
Beautiful garden restaurant, innovative food, great wines. A necessary stop when in Tallinn.
Must be restaurant and cafe with the best view of Salzburg.
Delicious... would love to come back during warmer days so I can sit outside and enjoy the view to the lake.
Stayed at this hotel. They have really good scones! Hotel badly in need of an uplift. Nice garden. Very good and huge breakfasts.
The noodle bowls are quite huge. The rice sets are good value for money.

tip.text: We enjoyed the charcoal steamboat here with the tom yam base soup.
Had a ritzy afternoon 'sky tea' here. Great experience, amazing views, good food and wonderful ambiance.

tip.text: Beautiful and historical restaurant setting and order the traditional dish choucroute!
Very central in Tallinn, the hotel has 2 entrances at Pik and Lai streets. Breakfasts are quite good and everytime in different rooms.
Love the prawn noodle here...

I always eat here with the family when I am in Cebu. Buko pandan, mango cream, so good! The rest of the Filipino dishes are great. Can't pick a fave since we always order different stuff all the time.
Hotel room was quite big and comfortable, just perfect for my day layover in Dubai. I was there end of July so the whole city and country was an open sauna! There is a pool on the top floor.
Has very nice view to the bridge and river, and food presentation may not be the best, but they are super tasty! Not cheap though, but then again this is Switzerland. Only parking is cheap.
Food is okay but the interior is AWESOME. Beautiful, historical, vaulted cellar restaurant with several interior design themes going on at every corner. Very touristy but lots of locals as well.
A Bavarian hotel with a real Bavarian interior and restaurant. Located in the forest, near a train station, free wifi, free parking...
A very traditional Austrian cafe house that you cannot help but smile. I tried the Tomaselliums Kaffee with Mozart liquor. Very good!

I very much enjoyed my fine dinner here while being serenaded by the Salon Trio with classical music. Great food, lovely place, good service, wonderful entertainment. The skylight ceiling is gorgeous.
I had the reindeer rumpsteak which was very very good! The interior was indeed a taste of Lapland.
This is the chicest street of Helsinki! Great place during warmer days to sit outside with a glass of wine and people watch.
A very charming pretty little hotel! The breakfast was grand. Loved the bed.
Nice terrace near the water and those ciders are always great to quench a thirst! Scroll down to the end part to
A nice restaurant on the beach where you can catch the Samos sunset. We enjoyed our very Greek evening dinner here. Loved the ambiance. Thank you for the desserts!
The nice thing with Profile Cafe Bar are their sunbeds because they have soft mattresses on top! Comfy =) We enjoyed the Greek Salad though and our lazy beach afternoon here.
I loved the beach 'wooden trellis' setting and the food here is quite good. We very much enjoyed our dinner here.
I loved dining in historical buildings! And yes, those tissue packets, you need them.
The queues here are unbelievably long! But the hainanese chicken rice was quite good though.

tip.text: A bellota and a rioja is always a good idea. My go to place when I have my jamon iberico bellota cravings.
My sister and I had fun getting drunk with tea here =)
Nevermind the ridiculously priced drinks, we came here for the views =)

tip.text: Loved the experience here! Reminiscing my college days 2 decades ago.

Very nice to sit outside when the weather is lovely with fresh mint tea and a lemon tart.
The dimsum dumplings are very good!
You really just come here for the views.
This is one of those restaurants that has an easy location on Suria KLCC with views directly to the lake and park. I tried Malaysia's national dish: Nasi Lemak =)

tip.text: Nice place to shop for local crafts and street food.
We mistook this as a restaurant but glad we made the detour =) Beautiful temple!
The 'appelbol' is always a good idea at Graaf Floris. It is a favourite =)
A great place to quickly stop over for the typical Catalan/Spanish chocolate (paired with churros, bread or a croissant - you dunk it in) in an old world setting.
We loved our al-fresco lunch here at the terrace. A relaxed and great place to be.
Beautiful classic period style restaurant with stylish ambiance, Lunch here was perfect. Do not worry about the see-through toilets =)

location.address: Wolvengracht 32 Rue du Fossé aux Loups

tip.text: I very much enjoyed my stay here. The glass windows and terrace with panoramic views to Girona made me book this hotel.

venue.name: AC Hotel Palau de Bellavista by Marriott

tip.text: I have enjoyed this bustling place in La Boqueria. I ordered the pulpo gallega! Tourist prices here though.
Loved the farm house garden setting and the food here is delicious. A very well-deserved lunch indeed.
Lovely food and the chef is very zorgzaam, charming and talkative =) 'Twas a wonderful dinner to end the year (2012).
A very pretty place in Amsterdam. We loved the royal afternoon tea! Elegant, beautiful setting and refreshing.
Another great place in Amsterdam for summer. Different ambiance: Dining in a refurbished ferry boat. Loved the fresh produce. Lovely dinner.
Chic place to be. Loved the airy modern industrial design going on and the spa-like toilets are beautiful! Great place to lunch.
Loved the laid back atmosphere and the terrace lounge concept. Great place during summer! Good food. I will be back.
Beautiful place with gorgeous views! Too expensive coffee though but a great place all in all especially for first time Amsterdam visitors. I have been here twice, for lunch and in the evening.
